				<p>An <code>.env.example</code> file is provided in the root of this project to guide users on the
					necessary requirements for the application. To create a <code>.env</code> file from the example
					file, use the terminal in the project directory and run the following command:</p>

				<div class="card code-card mt-2">
					<div class="card-body">
						<code>cp .env.example .env</code>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="mt-3">Open the <code>.env</code> file and insert the required keys for the project, such as
