				<h3 id="database-management" class="mt-5">Database Management</h3>
				<h4 id="mongodb-setup" class="mt-3">MongoDB Setup</h4>
				<p>Configure MongoDB to store user interaction data, including uploaded resumes and generated career
					path suggestions. This enables the application to maintain a history of user interactions and
					provide better insights over time.</p>

				<h4 id="resume-upload-handling" class="mt-5">Resume Upload Handling</h4>
				<p>Implement functionality to handle resume file uploads securely and efficiently. Use Multer middleware
					for managing file uploads and ensure that uploaded files are stored in the designated directory.</p>

				<h4 id="career-path-analysis" class="mt-5">Career Path Analysis</h4>
				<p>Develop the core functionality to analyze uploaded resumes using OpenAI's API. Process the resume
					content, send it to OpenAI for analysis, and interpret the results to suggest suitable career paths.
				</p>
				<ol>
					<li><strong>Preparation of the Directive:</strong> A detailed directive is created, instructing the
						AI on how to analyze the resume. The directive includes specific instructions on generating a
						structured JSON response covering various aspects such as summary, career path, strong skills,
						suggested learning, suggested certifications, industry trends, and salary expectations.</li>
					<li><strong>Integration with OpenAI's API:</strong> The application uses the OpenAI API to process
						the resume content. This involves sending a POST request to the OpenAI endpoint with the
						prepared directive and the resume text.</li>
					<li><strong>Sending the Request:</strong> The POST request includes the model specification,
						messages, token limit, and headers for authorization and content type.</li>
					<li><strong>Receiving the Response:</strong> The OpenAI API processes the request and returns a
						response containing the AI-generated suggestions in JSON format.</li>
					<li><strong>Parsing the Response:</strong> The application parses the JSON response to extract the
						relevant information, ensuring it is well-formatted and free of errors.</li>
					<li><strong>Providing Career Suggestions:</strong> The parsed response is used to provide the user
						with career path suggestions, including a summary, career path overview, strong skills,
						suggested learning, suggested certifications, industry trends, and salary expectations.</li>
				</ol>

				<h4 id="error-handling" class="mt-5">Error Handling</h4>
				<p>Implement robust error handling to manage unexpected issues gracefully. Ensure that errors are logged
					and that users receive appropriate feedback in case of problems during file upload, API interaction,
					or other operations.</p>

				<h4 id="testing-and-validation" class="mt-5">Testing and Validation</h4>
				<p>Conduct thorough testing to validate the functionality of the application. Perform unit tests,
					integration tests, and user acceptance tests to ensure the application meets all requirements and
					provides a seamless user experience.</p>

